{"session_id": "2fd36ba5-ba5e-49de-ba15-f78653c66946", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\enyan\\.claude\\projects\\d--projects-claudeCodeLearn-python-sdk-main\\2fd36ba5-ba5e-49de-ba15-f78653c66946.jsonl", "cwd": "d:\\projects\\claudeCodeLearn\\python-sdk-main", "permission_mode": "default", "hook_event_name": "PreToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "d:\\projects\\claudeCodeLearn\\python-sdk-main\\CLAUDE.md", "content": "# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n@AGENTS.md\n\n## Architecture\n\nThis is the Python SDK for the [Model Context Protocol (MCP)](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) \udce2\udc80\udc94 a standard for exposing tools, resources, and prompts to LLM clients. The `main` branch is a v2 pre-alpha rework; see `README.v2.md` for current docs.\n\n### Package layout\n\n```\nsrc/mcp/\n  server/\n    lowlevel/    # Low-level Server: explicit on_* handler functions, full control\n    mcpserver/   # High-level MCPServer: decorator API (@tool, @resource, @prompt)\n    auth/        # OAuth2/JWT auth server (handlers, middleware, provider interface)\n    sse.py / stdio.py / streamable_http.py / websocket.py  # transport implementations\n  client/\n    client.py    # Unified Client (wraps ClientSession + transport lifecycle)\n    session.py   # ClientSession \udce2\udc80\udc94 raw MCP protocol layer\n    auth/        # OAuth2 client authentication\n    _memory.py   # InMemoryTransport for testing\n  shared/\n    session.py   # BaseSession: core send/receive/request-response loop\n    memory.py    # create_client_server_memory_streams \udce2\udc80\udc94 used by InMemoryTransport\n    exceptions.py / auth.py / message.py / _otel.py \udce2\udc80\u5412n  types/         # Pydantic models for every MCP protocol type\n  cli/           # mcp CLI (`mcp dev`, `mcp install`, etc.)\n  os/            # Platform-specific utilities (posix / win32)\n```\n\n### Two server layers\n\n**`Server`** (`src/mcp/server/lowlevel/server.py`) \udce2\udc80\udc94 constructor takes `on_*` callables for each MCP request type. Use when you need precise control or are building infrastructure.\n\n**`MCPServer`** (`src/mcp/server/mcpserver/server.py`) \udce2\udc80\udc94 wraps `Server` and exposes `@tool`, `@resource`, `@prompt`, and `@server.lifespan` decorators. This is the primary API for application developers and most examples.\n\n### High-level client\n\n**`Client`** (`src/mcp/client/client.py`) accepts a `Server | MCPServer` for in-memory connections (testing), a URL string for Streamable HTTP, or a custom `Transport` object. It wraps `ClientSession` and manages the transport lifecycle.\n\n### Transport stack\n\nAll transports ultimately produce a pair of `(read_stream, write_stream)` passed to `Server.run()`. `BaseSession` owns the message pump; request/response correlation is handled by `ResponseRouter`. Transports available: stdio, SSE, Streamable HTTP, WebSocket, and in-memory (test-only).\n\n### In-memory testing pattern\n\nThe canonical test pattern avoids network I/O entirely:\n\n```python\nasync with Client(my_server) as client:\n    result = await client.call_tool(\"my_tool\", {\"arg\": \"value\"})\n```\n\n`Client(server)` wires up `InMemoryTransport` \udce2\udc86\udc92 `create_client_server_memory_streams` \udce2\udc86\udc92 server task running in the background. See `tests/client/test_client.py` for reference patterns.\n\n### Public API surface\n\n`src/mcp/__init__.py` defines `__all__`. Adding a symbol there is a deliberate API decision. Most protocol types live in `src/mcp/types/`; server and client classes are re-exported from `src/mcp/server/` and `src/mcp/client/` respectively.\n"}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01GsLutgC4bR5eNnEwFwzvb9"}
