**`Server`** (`src/mcp/server/lowlevel/server.py`) \udce2\udc80\udc94 constructor takes `on_*` callables for each MCP request type. Use when you need precise control or are building infrastructure.\n\n**`MCPServer`** (`src/mcp/server/mcpserver/server.py`) \udce2\udc80\udc94 wraps `Server` and exposes `@tool`, `@resource`, `@prompt`, and `@server.lifespan` decorators. This is the primary API for application developers and most examples.\n\n### High-level client\n\n**`Client`** (`src/mcp/client/client.py`) accepts a `Server | MCPServer` for in-memory connections (testing), a URL string for Streamable HTTP, or a custom `Transport` object. It wraps `ClientSession` and manages the transport lifecycle.\n\n### Transport stack\n\nAll transports ultimately produce a pair of `(read_stream, write_stream)` passed to `Server.run()`. `BaseSession` owns the message pump; request/response correlation is handled by `ResponseRouter`. Transports available: stdio, SSE, Streamable HTTP, WebSocket, and in-memory (test-only).\n\n### In-memory testing pattern\n\nThe canonical test pattern avoids network I/O entirely:\n\n```python\nasync with Client(my_server) as client:\n    result = await client.call_tool(\"my_tool\", {\"arg\": \"value\"})\n```\n\n`Client(server)` wires up `InMemoryTransport` \udce2\udc86\udc92 `create_client_server_memory_streams` \udce2\udc86\udc92 server task running in the background. See `tests/client/test_client.py` for reference patterns.\n\n### Public API surface\n\n`src/mcp/__init__.py` defines `__all__`. Adding a symbol there is a deliberate API decision. Most protocol types live in `src/mcp/types/`; server and client classes are re-exported from `src/mcp/server/` and `src/mcp/client/` respectively.\n"}, "tool_response": {"type": "update", "filePath": "d:\\projects\\claudeCodeLearn\\python-sdk-main\\CLAUDE.md", "content": "# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n@AGENTS.md\n\n## Arc