ing for Streamable HTTP, or a custom `Transport` object. It wraps `ClientSession` and manages the transport lifecycle.\n\n### Transport stack\n\nAll transports ultimately produce a pair of `(read_stream, write_stream)` passed to `Server.run()`. `BaseSession` owns the message pump; request/response correlation is handled by `ResponseRouter`. Transports available: stdio, SSE, Streamable HTTP, WebSocket, and in-memory (test-only).\n\n### In-memory testing pattern\n\nThe canonical test pattern avoids network I/O entirely:\n\n```python\nasync with Client(my_server) as client:\n    result = await client.call_tool(\"my_tool\", {\"arg\": \"value\"})\n```\n\n`Client(server)` wires up `InMemoryTransport` \udce2\udc86\udc92 `create_client_server_memory_streams` \udce2\udc86\udc92 server task running in the background. See `tests/client/test_client.py` for reference patterns.\n\n### Public API surface\n\n`src/mcp/__init__.py` defines `__all__`. Adding a symbol there is a deliberate API decision. Most protocol types live in `src/mcp/types/`; server and client classes are re-exported from `src/mcp/server/` and `src/mcp/client/` respectively.\n", "structuredPatch": [{"oldStart": 1, "oldLines": 1, "newStart": 1, "newLines": 61, "lines": ["+# CLAUDE.md", "+", "+This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.", "+", " @AGENTS.md", "+", "+## Architecture", "+", "+This is the Python SDK for the [Model Context Protocol (MCP)](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) \udce2\udc80\udc94 a standard for exposing tools, resources, and prompts to LLM clients. The `main` branch is a v2 pre-alpha rework; see `README.v2.md` for current docs.", "+", "+### Package layout", "+", "+```", "+src/mcp/", "+  server/", "+    lowlevel/    # Low-level Server: explicit on_* handler functions, full control", "+    mcpserver/   # High-level MCPServer: decorator API (@tool, @resource, @prompt)", "+    auth/        # OAuth2/JWT auth server (handlers, middleware, pr