files, and a few representative source files to understand the architecture. Report findings thoroughly so I can write a good CLAUDE.md.", "agentId": "ad3d1bf8a432540c2", "agentType": "Explore", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed report.\n\n## Codebase Analysis Report\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the **claude_code_toy_marketplace** project, here are my findings:\n\n---\n\n### 1. AVAILABLE COMMANDS\n\n**Build & Development Commands** (from package.json):\n- `npm run dev` - Start local development server with Vite (runs on port 8080)\n- `npm run build` - Production build with Vite\n- `npm run build:dev` - Development mode build\n- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint on the codebase\n- `npm run preview` - Preview production build locally\n\n**Supabase Commands** (from README_Supabase.md):\n- `supabase logout / supabase login` - Auth management\n- `supabase db reset` - Reset local database with migrations\n- `supabase start` - Start local Supabase server (runs on http://localhost:54323)\n- `supabase migration new [name]` - Create new database migration\n- `supabase db push` - Deploy migrations to remote project\n- `supabase link --project-ref $SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF` - Link to remote project\n\n---\n\n### 2. HIGH-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE\n\nThis is a **React-based P2P Toy Marketplace** web application with real-time messaging capabilities.\n\n**Architecture Pattern: Client-Side React SPA with Backend-as-a-Service (BaaS)**\n\n**Core Layers:**\n\n1. **Frontend Layer**: React 18 + TypeScript\n   - Single Page Application built with Vite and React Router v6\n   - Component-based UI using shadcn/ui (Radix UI + Tailwind CSS)\n   \n2. **State Management & Data Fetching**:\n   - TanStack React Query (v5) for server state management\n   - Custom React hooks for business logic (useAuth, usePublicProducts, useSavedProducts, etc.)\n   - React Context API for application state (PresenceProvider for real-time user presence)\n\n3. **Backend Layer**: Supabase (Firebase alternative)\n   - PostgreSQL database\n   - Authentication (Google OAuth integration)\n   - Real-time subscriptions via WebSockets\n   - Row-Level Security (RLS) policies\n   - Custom RPC functions for secure data access\n\n4. **UI/UX Layer**:\n   - shadcn/ui component library (40+ pre-built components)\n   - Tailwind CSS for styling\n   - Dark mode support via next-themes\n   - Mobile-responsive design\n\n---\n\n### 3. PROJECT STRUCTURE & KEY MODULES\n\n```\nsrc/\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 pages/                    # Page components (route views)\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 Index.tsx             # Home page\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 Categories.tsx        # Products listing/filtering\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 ProductDetail.tsx     # Single product view with messaging\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 CreateListing.tsx     # Listing creation page\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 CreateListingForm.tsx # Form for creating/editing products with image upload\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 ConversationList.tsx  # Messages/conversations inbox\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 ConversationDetail.tsx # Individual conversation thread\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 SavedItems.tsx        # User's saved products\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 Profile.tsx           # User profile & listings\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 Auth.tsx              # Sign in/sign up/reset password\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\u