82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 FilterSheet.tsx       # Sorting/filtering UI\n\udce2\udc94\udc82\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 hooks/                    # Custom React hooks\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 useAuth.tsx           # Auth state management\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 usePublicProducts.tsx # Fetch & manage public products with sorting\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 useSavedProducts.tsx  # Manage saved/wishlist items\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 useUserProducts.tsx   # Manage user's own products\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 useUnreadMessagesCount.tsx # Track unread message count\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 use-toast.ts          # Toast notifications hook\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 use-mobile.tsx        # Mobile breakpoint detection\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 useUserSavedProducts.tsx # User's saved products list\n\udce2\udc94\udc82\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 contexts/                 # React Context providers\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 PresenceProvider.tsx  # Real-time user presence tracking via Supabase channels\n\udce2\udc94\udc82\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 integrations/             # Third-party integrations\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 supabase/\n\udce2\udc94\udc82       \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 client.ts         # Supabase client initialization (auto-switches dev/prod)\n\udce2\udc94\udc82       \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 types.ts          # Auto-generated TypeScript types from Supabase schema\n\udce2\udc94\udc82\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 lib/                      # Utility functions\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 imageUtils.ts         # Image resizing & compression\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 utils.ts              # General utilities\n\udce2\udc94\udc82\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 assets/                   # Static assets\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 marketplace-logo.png\n\udce2\udc94\udc82\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 App.tsx                   # Root component with routing setup\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 main.tsx                  # React DOM render entry point\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 index.css                 # Global styles\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 vite-env.d.ts             # Vite type definitions\n\udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 App.css                   # App component styles\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. CONFIGURATION FILES\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| **tsconfig.json** | Root TypeScript config with path aliases (@/* \udce2\udc86\udc92 ./src/*) |\n| **tsconfig.app.json** | App-specific TypeScript settings (target ES2020, loose strict mode) |\n| **tsconfig.node.json** | Build/node scripts TypeScript settings |\n| **eslint.config.js** | ESLint configuration for React + TypeScript linting |\n| **vite.config.ts** | Vite bundler config (SWC for fast transpiling, path alias setup) |\n| **tailwind.config.ts** | Tailwind CSS configuration with custom theme colors & animations |\n| **postcss.config.js** | PostCSS plugins (Tailwind + Autoprefixer) |\n| **components.json** | shadcn/ui CLI configuration for component installation |\n| **index.html** | HTML entry point with root div and module script |\n\n---\n\n### 5. KEY TECHNOLOGIES & LIBRARIES\n\n**Core Framework:**\n- React 18.3.1 (UI framework)\n- React Router DOM 6.30.1 (Client-side routing)\n- TypeScript 5.8.3 (Type safety)\n- Vite 5.4.19 (Fast build tool)\n\n**State & Data:**\n- TanStack React Query 5.83.0 (Server state management)\n- Supabase JS Client 2.56.0 (Backend + database)\n- React Hook Form 7.61.1 (Form state)\n- Zod 3.25.76 (Schema validation)\n\n**UI Components & Styling:**\n- shadcn/ui (Radix UI primitives + Tailwind)\n- Tailwind CSS 3.4.17 (Utility-first CSS)\n- Lucide React 0.462.0 (Icon library)\n- Sonner 1.7.4 (Toast notifications)\n- Embla Carousel 8.6.0 (Image carousel)\n- Recharts 2.15.4 (Charts)\n- next-themes 0.3.0 (Dark mode)\n\n**Utilities:**\n- date-fns 3.6.0 (Date manipulation)\n- clsx 2.1.1 (Class name utility)\n- tailwind-merge 2.6.0 (CSS conflict resolution)\n\n**Development:**\n- ESLint 9.32.0 (Code linting)\n- Lovable-tagger (Component tagging for AI tools)\n\n---\n\n### 6. KEY PATTERNS & ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS\n\n**Data Flow Pattern:**\n```\nPages (React Components) \udce2\udc86\udc92 Custom Hooks (usePublicProducts, useAuth, etc.)\n  \udce2\udc86\udc92 Supabase RPC Functions \udce2\udc86\udc92 PostgreSQL Database\n```\n\n**Authentication:**\n- Google OAuth via Supabase Auth\n- Session persisted in localStorage\n- useAuth hook manages current user state globally\n\n**Real-Time Features:**\n- Supabase Channels for presence tracking (PresenceProvider)\n- WebSocket-based messaging\n- RLS policies for data security\n\n**Image Handling:**\n- Image compression/resizing in `imageUtils.ts`\n- Uploaded to Supabase Storage\n- Support for multiple images per product\n\n**Secure Data Access:**\n- RPC functions used instead of direct table queries (avoids RLS issues with JOINs)\n- Examples: `get_public_products()`, `get_public_product_detail()`, `is_product_owner()`, `get_user_conversation_for_product()`\n\n**Naming Conventions:**\n- **Files**: Camel case (CreateListingForm.tsx, NavigationBar.tsx)\n- **Components**: PascalCase exports\n- **Types**: Exported interfaces/types\n- **Database functions**: snake_case\n\n**Code Organization Principles:**\n- Pages handle routing & page layout\n- Components handle UI rendering\n- Hooks handle business logic & data fetching\n- Contexts provide app-wide state (presence)\n- Integrations isolated in /integrations folder\n\n---\n\n### 7. EXISTING DOCUMENTATION\n\n**README Files:**\n- `README.md` - Minimal placeholder\n- `README_Lovable.md` - Development guidelines (naming conventions, RPC usage, no PII commits)\n- `README_Supabase.md` - Supabase setup & migration commands\n- `README_TODO.md` - \"implement image upload feature in conversation\" (planned feature)\n\n**Configuration Examples:**\n- `.mcp.json.example*` - MCP (Model Context Protocol) configuration templates\n\n---\n\n### 8. SUPABASE DATABASE STRUCTURE\n\n**Key Tables:**\n- `conversations` - P2P message threads between buyers/sellers\n- `messages` - Individual messages within conversations\n- `message_status` - Read/unread tracking per user\n- `products` - Listings with details (price, description, color, leather, year, stamp, location)\n- `product_images` - Image URLs associated with products\n- (Implied) `users` - User profiles from Supabase Auth\n\n**Security:**\n- Row-Level Security (RLS) enabled\n- Custom RPC functions for safe cross-table queries\n- Google OAuth integration\n\n---\n\n### 9. DEPLOYMENT SETUP\n\n- **Development**: Local Supabase (http://localhost:54321) + Vite dev server (port 8080)\n- **Production**: Remote Supabase project + Vite build output\n- **Auto-switching**: Client detects localhost vs. production and uses appropriate endpoints\n- **Credentials stored in**: `client.ts` (embedded keys), `.mcp.json` (server-side), `config.toml` (Supabase config)\n\n---\n\n### 10. NOTABLE ARCHITECTURE INSIGHTS\n\n1. **Lovable-generated project**: Uses Lovable CLI with tagger for AI-assisted development\n2. **BaaS approach**: No custom backend server; relies entirely on Supabase for business logic\n3. **Type safety**: Auto-generated TypeScript types from Supabase schema (types.ts)\n4. **Real-time presence**: WebSocket-based user online status tracking\n5. **Mobile-first**: Uses Tailwind's responsive classes and mobile hook detection\n6. **Component library**: Extensive use of pre-built shadcn/ui components\n7. **Local dev parity**: Supabase local development environment mirrors production schema\n\n---\n\nThis is a modern, well-structured React marketplace with BaaS backend, emphasizing real-time messaging, image handling, and user presence tracking. The codebase follows clear separation of concerns with hooks managing data, components handling UI, and pages composing them for routes."}], "totalDurationMs": 63531, "totalTokens": 40058, "totalToolUseCount": 41, "usage": {"input_tokens": 7, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 2563, "cache_read_input_tokens": 34421, "output_tokens": 3067, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 2563}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [{"input_tokens": 7, "output_tokens": 3067, "cache_read_input_tokens": 34421, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 2563, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 2563, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "type": "message"}], "speed": "standard"}, "toolStats": {"readCount": 26, "searchCount": 1, "bashCount": 14, "editFileCount": 0, "linesAdded": 0, "linesRemoved": 0, "otherToolCount": 0}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01AgKnQZVymMnN4uMJa7Wp9n"}
