{"session_id": "bf6af7e9-b909-4d0e-a196-01ca96c366a6", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\enyan\\.claude\\projects\\d--projects-claudeCodeLearn-claude-code-toy-marketplace-initial\\bf6af7e9-b909-4d0e-a196-01ca96c366a6.jsonl", "cwd": "d:\\projects\\claudeCodeLearn\\claude_code_toy_marketplace-initial", "permission_mode": "default", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Read", "tool_input": {"file_path": "d:\\projects\\claudeCodeLearn\\claude_code_toy_marketplace-initial\\README_Supabase.md"}, "tool_response": {"type": "text", "file": {"filePath": "d:\\projects\\claudeCodeLearn\\claude_code_toy_marketplace-initial\\README_Supabase.md", "content": "### Supabase Credential in the project \n- clients.ts: SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY\n- .mcp.json: PROJECT_REF, SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN\n- config.toml; PROJECT_ID\n\n### Supabase Setup\n- Google Auth Provider enable.\n - Go to Authentication > Sign in / Providers > \n\n### Local development\n#### Re-apply existing migrations \nsupabase logout\nsupabase login\nsupabase db reset\nsupabase start \n> http://localhost:54323\n> This is the local supabase server for your to invoke API against\n\n#### Add new migrations \nsupabase migration new xxxxx_table\n> update the sql in the xxxxx_table\nsupabase db reset\n\n#### Deploy to remote project \nsupabase logout\nsupabase login\nSUPABASE_PROJECT_REF=XXXXX\nsupabase link --debug --project-ref $SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF\nsupabase db push\n", "numLines": 30, "startLine": 1, "totalLines": 30}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_013pC3eirQgCm3qgVj65Ae4X"}
{"session_id": "bf6af7e9-b909-4d0e-a196-01ca96c366a6", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\enyan\\.claude\\projects\\d--projects-claudeCodeLearn-claude-code-toy-marketplace-initial\\bf6af7e9-b909-4d0e-a196-01ca96c366a6.jsonl", "cwd": "d:\\projects\\claudeCodeLearn\\claude_code_toy_marketplace-initial", "permission_mode": "acceptEdits", "hook_event_name": "PreToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "d:\\projects\\claudeCodeLearn\\claude_code_toy_marketplace-initial\\CLAUDE.md", "content": "# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\n# Development\nnpm run dev          # Start Vite dev server on port 8080\nnpm run build        # Production build\nnpm run lint         # Run ESLint\n\n# Supabase local dev (re-apply existing migrations)\nsupabase logout && supabase login\nsupabase db reset    # Resets local DB and applies all migrations\nsupabase start       # Local Supabase server at http://localhost:54323\n\n# Supabase: add a new migration\nsupabase migration new <name>   # then edit the generated SQL file\nsupabase db reset\n\n# Supabase: deploy to remote\nsupabase link --project-ref $SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF\nsupabase db push\n```\n\n## Architecture\n\nThis is a React 18 + TypeScript SPA (Vite) backed entirely by **Supabase** (PostgreSQL + Auth + Realtime + Storage). There is no custom backend server.\n\n**Data flow:**\n```\nPages \udce2\udc86\udc92 Custom Hooks \udce2\udc86\udc92 Supabase RPC / client \udce2\udc86\udc92 PostgreSQL (with RLS)\n```\n\n**Key layers:**\n- `src/pages/` \udce2\udc80\udc94 Route-level components; compose hooks and UI components\n- `src/hooks/` \udce2\udc80\udc94 All data fetching and business logic (React Query + Supabase)\n- `src/components/` \udce2\udc80\udc94 Reusable UI; `components/ui/` is shadcn/ui (do not edit manually)\n- `src/contexts/PresenceProvider.tsx` \udce2\udc80\udc94 Real-time user presence via Supabase Channels\n- `src/integrations/supabase/` \udce2\udc80\udc94 Supabase client (`client.ts` auto-switches local/prod) and auto-generated types (`types.ts`)\n- `src/lib/imageUtils.ts` \udce2\udc80\udc94 Client-side image resizing/compression before upload to Supabase Storage\n\n**Authentication:** Google OAuth via Supabase Auth. `useAuth` hook provides the current user globally.\n\n**Messaging:** Conversations and messages are stored in `conversations`, `messages`, and `message_status` tables. Real-time updates use Supabase subscriptions.\n\n## Critical Patterns\n\n**Always use RPC functions for cross-table data access.** Direct table queries with JOINs silently return no data when RLS policies block the join. Check existing RPC functions first (e.g., `get_public_products`, `get_public_product_detail`, `is_product_owner`, `get_user_conversation_for_product`) and reuse or create new ones as needed. Add new RPC functions via a Supabase migration.\n\n**File naming:** camelCase for all files \udce2\udc80\udc94 e.g., `CreateListingForm.tsx`, `usePublicProducts.tsx`.\n\n**Type safety:** `src/integrations/supabase/types.ts` is auto-generated from the Supabase schema. Do not edit it manually; regenerate it after schema changes.\n\n**Supabase credentials** are stored in three places: `client.ts` (URL + anon key), `.mcp.json` (project ref + access token), and `supabase/config.toml` (project ID). Do not commit PII such as email addresses.\n"}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01PG3zY2oSwcpRPgFruWefzT"}
