{"session_id": "456bd2ed-dd19-4edc-98a1-65b0c2b67bff", "transcript_path": "C:\\Users\\enyan\\.claude\\projects\\d--projects-claude-microPad\\456bd2ed-dd19-4edc-98a1-65b0c2b67bff.jsonl", "cwd": "d:\\projects\\claude_microPad", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Agent", "tool_input": {"description": "Explore firmware and project structure", "prompt": "Explore the project at d:\\projects\\claude_microPad. I need to understand:\n1. The full content of firmware/claude_macropad/claude_macropad.ino - what keys are defined, how actions are mapped, what protocol is used for USB HID\n2. Any existing config files or communication protocols\n3. The hooks/ directory - what hooks exist and what they do\n4. The overall project structure\n\nPlease read all relevant files and report:\n- How key actions are currently hardcoded in the firmware\n- What the data structures look like for key mappings\n- Whether there's any existing config/communication mechanism between host and device\n- File sizes and structure of the hooks directory\n\nBe thorough - read the full firmware file.", "subagent_type": "Explore"}, "tool_response": {"status": "completed", "prompt": "Explore the project at d:\\projects\\claude_microPad. I need to understand:\n1. The full content of firmware/claude_macropad/claude_macropad.ino - what keys are defined, how actions are mapped, what protocol is used for USB HID\n2. Any existing config files or communication protocols\n3. The hooks/ directory - what hooks exist and what they do\n4. The overall project structure\n\nPlease read all relevant files and report:\n- How key actions are currently hardcoded in the firmware\n- What the data structures look like for key mappings\n- Whether there's any existing config/communication mechanism between host and device\n- File sizes and structure of the hooks directory\n\nBe thorough - read the full firmware file.", "agentId": "a351d2f9ec501d820", "agentType": "Explore", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Project Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Claude microPad project. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **Firmware File: claude_macropad.ino** (6,849 bytes)\n\n**Complete Key Action Mappings (Currently Active - Test Mode):**\nThe firmware currently has a test mapping sending numeric keys 0-9:\n```\nGP0 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_0 (number 0)\nGP1 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_1 (number 1)\nGP2 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_2 (number 2)\nGP3 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_3 (number 3)\nGP4 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_4 (number 4)\nGP5 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_5 (number 5)\nGP6 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_6 (number 6)\nGP7 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_7 (number 7)\nGP8 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_8 (number 8)\nGP9 \udce2\udc86\udc92 HID_KEY_9 (number 9)\n```\n\n**Commented Intended Mapping (Final Design):**\n```\nGP0: Ctrl+C (Terminate)\nGP1: Shift+Tab (Change Permission Mode)\nGP2: Ctrl+E (Explain)\nGP3: UP Arrow\nGP4: Enter/Return\nGP5: Ctrl+T (Show Todo)\nGP6: / (Slash Command)\nGP7: DOWN Arrow\nGP8: Win+Tab (Switch Window)\nGP9: ESC (Encoder Press)\nGP20: Encoder CLK\nGP21: Encoder DT\n```\n\n**USB HID Protocol Details:**\n- Uses **Adafruit TinyUSB** library with `TUD_HID_REPORT_DESC_KEYBOARD()`\n- Custom `KeyboardEmulator` class that handles:\n  - Modifier keys (Ctrl, Shift, Alt, GUI) automatically detected from HID codes 0xE0-0xE7\n  - Simultaneous 3-key combos (modifiers + up to 6 regular keycodes)\n  - Proper USB polling at 2ms intervals\n  - USB endpoint stability checking before sending key releases\n- USB report format: 1 byte modifiers + 6 bytes keycode array (standard USB HID keyboard spec)\n\n**Data Structure for Key Mappings:**\n```c\nconst uint8_t BTN_KEYS[10][3] = {\n  {HID_KEY_X, modifier_or_0, 0},  // Each button has 3 bytes max\n  ...\n}\n```\nEach row is a 3-element array where:\n- Element 0: Main key or first modifier\n- Element 1: Second key or modifier\n- Element 2: Third key or unused\nThe array is processed to extract modifiers (0xE0-0xE7) and regular keycodes separately.\n\n**Debouncing:**\n- Button debounce: 20ms time-based debounce\n- Encoder debounce: 5ms stable time window + orthogonal state machine (ENC_TABLE)\n- Encoder: EC11 rotary encoder with 4 steps per detent, sends Up/Down arrows on completion\n\n**LED Control:**\n- 2 RGB LEDs (common-anode, inverted logic: LOW=on, HIGH=off)\n- GPIO pins: [2, 3, 4, 28, 27, 26] for [R1, G1, B1, R2, G2, B2]\n- States via Serial command: T=Blue (Thinking), C=Green (Completed), E=Red (Error), I=Green (Idle)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Config & Communication Protocols**\n\n**Host-to-Device Communication:**\n- **Serial Protocol**: USB CDC (virtual COM port) at 9600 baud\n- **Direction**: Host sends single ASCII character commands to device\n- **Command Set:**\n  - `T` = Thinking (blue LED) - used for tool execution\n  - `C` = Completed (green LED) - successful completion\n  - `E` = Error (red LED) - permission denied, tool failure\n  - `I` = Idle (green LED) - normal state, manual interrupt\n- **No device-to-host communication** - purely one-way status feedback\n\n**Device-to-Host (Key Events):**\n- Standard USB HID keyboard protocol\n- No custom protocol - behaves like a regular mechanical keyboard\n\n**Configuration Mechanism:**\n- **Firmware:** Key mappings are completely hardcoded in the `BTN_KEYS` array in the .ino file\n- **Host Integration:** Via Claude Code hooks that execute on various Claude Code events\n- **No dynamic runtime config** - changes require firmware recompilation\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Hooks Directory Analysis**\n\n**Directory Size:** 799,033 bytes (mostly debug.log)\n\n**Files:**\n- **led_hook.py** (2,225 bytes) - Main hook script\n  - Single-purpose: Maps Claude Code events to LED color commands\n  - Event mapping:\n    - `UserPromptSubmit`, `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse` \udce2\udc86\udc92 T (blue/thinking)\n    - `Stop` (completed) \udce2\udc86\udc92 C (green)\n    - `PostToolUseFailure`, `StopFailure`, `PermissionDenied` \udce2\udc86\udc92 E (red)\n    - `Notification` with `permission_prompt` \udce2\udc86\udc92 E (red)\n    - `Stop` with `user_interrupt` reason \udce2\udc86\udc92 I (green/idle)\n  - Reads event JSON from stdin\n  - Writes single byte command to serial port COM4 at 9600 baud\n  - Logs all events to debug.log for troubleshooting\n  - Gracefully handles serial errors (never blocks Claude Code)\n\n- **debug.log** (799,033 bytes) - JSON event logging file\n  - Contains every hook execution with full event payload\n  - Used for debugging hook integration and event timing\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Overall Project Structure**\n\n```\nclaude_microPad/\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 firmware/\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 claude_macropad/\n\udce2\udc94\udc82       \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 claude_macropad.ino          [6,849 bytes] Main firmware\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 hooks/\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 led_hook.py                      [2,225 bytes] Status indicator hook\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 debug.log                        [799 KB] Event logging\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 modal/                               [CAD/3D models directory]\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 *.SLDPRT, *.STL, *.gcode        3D design files (SolidWorks)\n\udce2\udc94\udc82   \udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 test/\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 diagram.json                         Wokwi circuit simulation\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 README.md                            Hardware spec (Traditional Chinese)\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 CLAUDE.md                            Claude Code project guide\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 \udce6\udc8c\udc89\udce9\udc88\udc95\u96ff\udc88\u6485\udc80.drawio / .jpg               Button layout diagram\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 \u7481\udc82\u6579\u8404\udc9c\udc96.jpg                           Concept image\n\udce2\udc94\udc9c\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 buttonIcon/                          [7 PNG icons] Key labels\n\udce2\udc94\udc94\udce2\udc94\udc80\udce2\udc94\udc80 .claude/settings.local.json          Claude Code hook configuration\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Key Integration Points**\n\n**Hardware:**\n- Controller: YD-RP2040 (Raspberry Pi Pico-compatible)\n- 10 pushbuttons, 1 rotary encoder (EC11), 2 RGB LEDs\n- All GPIO assignments fixed in firmware\n\n**Software Integration:**\n1. **Arduino IDE** with Earle Philhower arduino-pico package\n2. **Adafruit TinyUSB** library for USB HID\n3. **pyserial** for host-side serial communication\n4. **Claude Code hooks** configuration in `~/.claude/settings.json` (defined in README.md)\n\n**Current Limitations:**\n- **No runtime configuration**: Key mappings are hardcoded, require recompilation to change\n- **No reverse channel**: Device cannot communicate back except through LEDs\n- **Test mode active**: Currently sends number keys instead of intended Claude shortcuts\n- **Single port**: COM4 is hardcoded in led_hook.py (requires manual editing for different systems)\n\nAll files are read-only examined. The firmware is feature-complete but in test mode; the hook system is fully functional and properly integrated."}], "totalDurationMs": 48424, "totalTokens": 29967, "totalToolUseCount": 14, "usage": {"input_tokens": 183, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1889, "cache_read_input_tokens": 25919, "output_tokens": 1976, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1889}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [{"input_tokens": 183, "output_tokens": 1976, "cache_read_input_tokens": 25919, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1889, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1889, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "type": "message"}], "speed": "standard"}, "toolStats": {"readCount": 6, "searchCount": 0, "bashCount": 8, "editFileCount": 0, "linesAdded": 0, "linesRemoved": 0, "otherToolCount": 0}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01RoV7cTvVuZgWzseE6xubVf"}
